Before writing any code, read CLAUDE.md completely.
Then check repomix-output.xml for current file state.
Follow every rule in CLAUDE.md.
Never return sensitive profile fields in API responses.
Always use lib/api.ts for frontend fetch calls.
Use httpx not requests in Python.
Check if a file already exists before creating it.

CodeGraph integration:
- CodeGraph is running via codegraph watch in the background
- Before editing any existing file, query codegraph to understand:
  - what functions exist in that file
  - what other files import it
  - what it calls/depends on
- Use codegraph_explore or codegraph_query tools before touching existing code

Frontend package management:
- Always use pnpm for any frontend install commands.
- Never use npm install or yarn add in the frontend/ directory.

Git workflow rules:
- Always create a feature branch before starting any new feature or file
  Branch naming: feat/feature-name, fix/bug-name, chore/task-name
- Commit after every completed file or logical unit of work
- Commit message format: type(scope): description
  Examples:
  feat(backend): add user profile SQLAlchemy model
  feat(agent): add profile extractor with Gemini
  fix(auth): handle expired Clerk JWT correctly
  chore(config): add ruff.toml and biome.json
- Never commit broken code — only commit when the file works
- Never commit .env files, chroma_db/, or metadata.db
- After finishing a feature branch, remind user to merge to main
